National Security Advisor Tom Donilon met with UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon to discuss the urgent situation in the Horn of Africa, particularly in Somalia. They emphasized the need for international contributions and efficient distribution of food and assistance to those in need. Donilon highlighted the crucial role of UN agencies like the World Food Program and UN Children's Fund, and pledged U.S. support. They also discussed the ongoing efforts in Sudan, Libya, and the broader Middle East. U.S. Ambassador to the UN Susan Rice was present at the meeting.